info.name: Salesforce CRM Analytics Connect API
info.description: This collection lets you access CRM Analytics features such as datasets, dashboards, and lenses programmatically using the [CRM Analytics REST API](https://developer.salesforce.com/docs/atlas.en-us.bi_dev_guide_rest.meta/bi_dev_guide_rest/bi_dev_guide_rest_resources.htm). Using the CRM Analytics REST API, you can: - Send queries directly to the CRM Analytics Platform. - Access datasets that have been imported into the CRM Analytics Platform. - Validate templates for CRM Analytics apps. - Run CRM Analytics dataflows, recipes, and connections. See [Run, Schedule, and Sync CRM Analytics Data with REST APIs](https://developer.salesforce.com/docs/atlas.en-us.bi_dev_guide_rest.meta/bi_dev_guide_rest/bi_run_schedule_sync_data.htm) - Retrieve a list of dataflow job nodes and details for each individual node. - Access XMD information. - Retrieve standard datasets. - Retrieve a list of dataset versions. - Manipulate synced datasets, also known as connected objects. - Work with data connectors. - Retrieve recipe metadata. - Retrieve collections of CRM Analytics resources. ## Get Started Click the button below and follow the instructions from the following sections: [](https://god.gw.postman.com/run-collection/12721794-da62aee9-0da3-4f68-9083-1e10118bc2dd?action=collection%2Ffork&source=rip_markdown&collection-url=entityId%3D12721794-da62aee9-0da3-4f68-9083-1e10118bc2dd%26entityType%3Dcollection%26workspaceId%3D23726644-d41e-4b33-8e61-5da39d151606) 1. Assign a value to the `loginUrl` collection variable based on your Salesforce Org type: | Login URL | Org Type | | --- | --- | | `https://test.salesforce.com` | Sandboxes or Scratch orgs. | | `https://login.salesforce.com` | Production, Trailhead Playground and Developer Edition orgs. | | Custom My Domain base URL | Org with a custom domain. | 1. Click **Get New Access Token** from the collection's **Authorization** tab. 1. When prompted to do so, log in to your Salesforce org and allow access to "Salesforce APIs Collection for Postman". 1. Copy the value of the `instance_url` field from the token details view. 1. Click **Use Token**. 1. Save the value that you copied in the `_endpoint` variable. 1. Click **Save** and you're good to go!
